Amine filtration system is a filtration technology that utilizes amine‑based adsorbents to capture and remove contaminants from gases or liquids. The system is lauded for its high adsorption efficiency, ease of operation, and versatility across a wide range of applications – from eliminating acidic gases and organic matter in petrochemical streams to mitigating heavy‑metal ion contamination in water treatment. Its chemical stability and ability to be regenerated under mild conditions make it a preferred choice for industries seeking sustainable and cost‑effective solutions.

