What is Amine Filtration?
Amine filtration employs specialized amine compounds as the active adsorbent media within cartridge‑type or modular filter units. When process streams pass through the media, the amine functional groups chemically bind with acidic gases (such as H₂S, SO₂) and organic contaminants, effectively purifying the stream. After a defined service interval, the media can be regenerated by applying a controlled temperature swing or mild chemical treatment, restoring its adsorption capacity and extending its operational lifespan. This regeneration capability not only reduces consumable costs but also aligns with circular‑economy objectives pursued by many manufacturers.

